messages.content: What is ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion?
ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion is an extension that allows users to easily use Stable Video Diffusion inside ComfyUI.
How can ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion be installed?

ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion can be installed either via ComfyUI Manager by selecting the 'ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion' custom node by author 'thecooltechguy', or manually by cloning the GitHub repository into the ComfyUI/custom_nodes/ directory and running the install.py script.
Which models need to be downloaded into 'ComfyUI/models/svd/' for ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion?

The following models need to be downloaded into 'ComfyUI/models/svd/' for ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion: svd.safetensors, svd_image_decoder.safetensors, svd_xt.safetensors, and svd_xt_image_decoder.safetensors.
What are the node types available in ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion?
The node types available in ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion are: SVDModelLoader, SVDSampler, SVDDecoder, and SVDSimpleImg2Vid.
What does the SVDSimpleImg2Vid node do?
The SVDSimpleImg2Vid node combines the SVDModelLoader, SVDSampler, and SVDDecoder nodes into a single node for easier use.
Is there an example workflow for image to video generation using ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion?
Yes, there is an example workflow for image to video generation using ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion, which can be found at https://comfyworkflows.com/workflows/5a4cd9fd-9685-4985-adb8-7be84e8636ad.
Is there an example workflow for high FPS image to video generation with frame interpolation using ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion?

Yes, there is an example workflow for high FPS image to video generation with frame interpolation using ComfyUI Stable Video Diffusion, which can be found at https://comfyworkflows.com/workflows/bf3b455d-ba13-4063-9ab7-ff1de0c9fa75.
